question: Find the Rhea and Interpro combinations in UniProtKB entries
expected_sparql:
SELECT 
    ?interpro
    ?rhea
FROM <http://sparql.uniprot.org/uniprot>
WHERE 
{
  ?protein up:reviewed true .
  ?protein up:annotation ?annotation .
  ?annotation up:catalyticActivity ?rhea .
  ?protein rdfs:seeAlso ?interpro .
  ?interpro up:database <http://purl.uniprot.org/database/InterPro> .
} ORDER BY ?rhea

            SELECT (DISTINCT ?protein) (DISTINCT ?rhea) (DISTINCT ?interpro) ?interpro_label
WHERE {
    ?protein up:annotation ?ca_annotation ;
            up:annotation/rdfs:seeAlso ?interpro .
    ?ca_annotation a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation ;
                  up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
    ?interpro up:database <http://purl.uniprot.org/database/InterPro> ;
              rdfs:label ?interpro_label .
    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?rhea), "http://purl.uniprot.org/rhea/"))
}

            LIMIT 20
